==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solstitial
<hw>Sol*sti"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>solstitialis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>solsticial</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a solstice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Happening at a solstice; esp. (with reference to the
northern hemisphere), happening at the summer solstice, or
midsummer.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Solstitial</xex> summer's heat.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solubility</ent>⟦br⟧
